faM_2mediator_comp_EA3

Quan Zhou

25/02/23

This is a Rmarkdown file documented the two mediator mediation model for family envrionments (composites) mediate the prediction polygenic scores towards academic achievement across compulsory education (age 7, 9, 12, 16).

The analysis can help identify which mediator variables play a significant role in mediating the relationship between the independent and dependent variables, and can provide information on the relative strength of the indirect effects of each mediator.

meidator 1: family SES mediator 2: one of the rest of family environments (composites)

PGS: educational attainment 3

library(lavaan)

EA3_Lee2018_no23andme_corrected_FRCT1_year7_parentalfeel1_gses_gta1 <- 

'
  gta1 ~ b1*year7_parentalfeel1 + b2*gses + c*EA3_Lee2018_no23andme_corrected_FRCT1

  year7_parentalfeel1 ~ a1*EA3_Lee2018_no23andme_corrected_FRCT1
  
  gses ~ a2*EA3_Lee2018_no23andme_corrected_FRCT1
  
  # Indirect effects
  indirect1 := a1*b1
  indirect2 := a2*b2
  
  # Total effect
  total := c + (a1*b1) + (a2*b2)
  
  # Residual variances
  year7_parentalfeel1 ~~ gses
'


fitEA3_Lee2018_no23andme_corrected_FRCT1_year7_parentalfeel1_gses_gta1 <- sem(EA3_Lee2018_no23andme_corrected_FRCT1_year7_parentalfeel1_gses_gta1, data = dat)
